President Cyril Ramaphosa will deliver the keynote address at the National Youth Day event on Sunday in Limpopo. • Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa will deliver the keynote address at the National Youth Day event on Sunday. Ramaphosa will pay tribute to the youth of 1976 at the Peter Mokaba Cricket Club in Polokwane. On June 1976, police shot and killed dozens of school children who were fighting for their right to quality education. The day has become known as Youth Day in South Africa.